ales reached  dollars the following year masco became a publicly traded company traded on the detroit stock exchange in  masco’s sales exceeded  dollars masco screw products grew into the masco corporation a large corporate holding company for numerous acquisitions small familyrun businesses were bought out by masco corporation with cash and stock in the parent corporation between  and  richard manoogian who succeeded his father as chief executive acquired  companies valued at a total of  billion alex manoogian and his wife donated the manoogian mansion to the city of detroit as the official residence of the mayor masco in the s s and sedit in  manoogian began redesigning the singlehandle washerless faucet the faucet he created was one of the very first singlehandle hotcold faucets it is now known as delta delta’s television advertisements were a first for any faucet and made the product a successful seller masco went on to capture the mass market as sales moved from plumbing wholesalers to retail stores these steps of production and marketing of the delta faucet began in  and four years later delta faucet’s annual sales exceeded a million dollars this was the last year that the company would be referred to as masco screw products company alex manoogian founder acted as president and chief operating officer coo from  until  in  his son richard joined the company richard having spent nine years with the company succeeded his father one year after the company moved to taylor michigan alex died on july   the same year that his son richard passed on his coo role to ray kennedy allowing him to assume the position of chief executive officer in response to kennedy’s death alan barry was appointed as masco’s president and coo on april   in  masco screw products company changed its name to masco corporation in  they moved to their current corporate headquarters in taylor michigan for the first time in  masco was listed on the new york stock exchange in  masco first appeared on the fortune  and masco’s annual sales exceeded one billion dollars for the first time ever in  one year later masco began manufacturing cabinets reorganizing in the s and sedit in  masco’s earnings did not grow for the first time in  years the next year however “in  earnings climbed again for this maker of faucets and diverse product mix of builders’ hardware because of increased housing starts and a strong doityourself market” in  masco purchased the remaining outstanding stock of flint  walling inc after purchasing  in  and controlling interest in  in  masco started a home furnishings division by buying henredon for  million and drexel heritage for  million other companies added to the division were lexington home brands hickorycraft marge carson la barge and marbro in  and fabric company robert allenametex in  in  universal furniture benchcraft and calstyle were added in a  million deal as well as sunbury textiles the division added berkline in  and sold marge carson and calstyle in  masco reorganized its numerous companies in  the specialty products divisions of masco industries and masco corporation combined to form trimas corporation three years after this merger trimas was listed on the new york stock exchange nyse the remainder of masco industries became masco tech inc and in  was listed on the nyse at that point in time three different masco companies existed masco corp masco tech and trimas corp two years later masco entered the services business trimas and masco tech merged to form one company offering a wide array of products masco announced a  for  stock split which was the ninth time the company had split its shares since  and was the th year in a row that its dividends were increased this merger left two companies masco tech and masco corpcitation needed in  masco sold most of its home furnishings division to investors for  billion creating a new company called lifestyle furnishings international in  masco involved itself in the architectural coatings business and the company’s annual sales topped five billion dollars for the first time   presentedit in  masco corp acquired arrow fastener co inc a hand tool company expanding its business in the hardware category in  masco tech was purchased by a heartland industrial partners a private equity firm and its name was changed to metaldyne metaldyne is headquartered in plymouth michigan masco also divested flint  walling inc this year to zoeller company in  masco corp or simply masco entered the windows business and had operating profits beyond a billion dollars late in the year masco announced it would write down the value of its stake in lifestyle furnishings international by  million since its equity share was only  percent with the rest being debt lifestyle the third largest furniture maker in the united states with  billion in sales had sold universal furniture to lacquer craft then masco announced furniture brands international would buy drexel heritage henredon and maitlandsmith for  million with management of berkline benchcraft and sunbury taking over those companies lifestyle continued to own lexington robert allenametex and the beacon hill showrooms in  masco’s annual sales topped ten billion dollars and masco increased its quarterly dividend for the th consecutive year this ranked them in the top ten publicly owned companies achieving increased annual consecutive dividends throughout his time with the company richard manoogian has achieved a net worth of approximately  million he has been ranked as high as number five on the forbes  list of richest manufacturers the manoogian family is no longer involved in the management of the company masco businessesedit cabinets and related productsedit north america denova kraftmaid cabinetry merillat quality cabinets starmark international moores furniture group ltd plumbing productsedit north america brizo brasscraft manufacturing company brasstech inc caldera spas delta faucet company endless pools ginger hot sp